author: Jenny Hsu
title: Oil Prices Rebound But Downside Ahead
text: 0146 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude oil prices are slightly higher but analysts say profit-taking will likely keep the prices in a tight range, “The Chinese players are back after a long break and some are just catching up. We expect the upside to be limited given U.S. inventory figures were larger than anticipated,” says Daniel Ang, an oil analyst at Phillip Futures. On Wednesday, the U.S. energy department reported an increase of 3.1 million barrels in crude stocks for the week ended Oct 2.
